<subSubSection id="781F2AAF511A9429514FB697963DDC07" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="1" pageNumber="16" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C36C56D0B6C8661FBB84C8C6D76CCB95" pageId="1" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41D65DA8335250AEA12FED35EADC4A02" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="1" pageNumber="16">
The nominate subgenus was characterized by 
<bibRefCitation id="40FFD17D91145772ECDD6C8DD52EE962" author="Hamilton, KGA" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="7" pageNumber="22" pagination="875 - 932" title="Contributions to the study of the world Macropsini (Rhynchota: Homoptera: Cicadellidae)." url="10.4039/Ent112875-9" volume="112" year="1980">Hamilton (1980)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="138F3A0428C6D9E8FED9D7FCEECBA0F4" author="Li, H" journalOrPublisher="Florida Entomologist" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" pagination="535 - 542" title="Leafhopper Subgenus Pediopsoides (Pediopsoides) (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae, Macropsinae) with Descriptions of Two New Species from Southern China." url="10.1653/024.095.0301" volume="95" year="2012">Li et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. It can be distinguished by the following combination of features: pronotal striations oblique, forewings with two anteapical cells, dorsal connective freely attached (fused in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="24A9C3DF9231CFA47958C0F6DEED0C40" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pediopsoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pediopsoides (Celopsis)" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Celopsis">
<pageBreakToken id="1A1CFFE41ACABD9ABDE5274AA718F1CA" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" start="start">Pediopsoides</pageBreakToken>
(Celopsis)
</taxonomicName>
) to tenth tergite, and male pygofer without multifid or additional spines [male pygofer spine bifid or with rounded lobe on inner margin basally in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="1A3E4F44674BD17ED0F4DA90C4091E5E" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pediopsoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pediopsoides (Sispocnis)" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sispocnis">Pediopsoides (Sispocnis)</taxonomicName>
, a small secondary pygofer spine posteriorly in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="8A86D979E53AD03598B84BE5A91BE1E6" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pediopsoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pediopsoides (Nanopsis)" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Nanopsis">Pediopsoides (Nanopsis)</taxonomicName>
, and male pygofer spine are multifid in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="DBCC2914F169C458AC218CFF1B1FBAE0" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pediopsoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pediopsoides (Kiamoncopsis)" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Kiamoncopsis">Pediopsoides (Kiamoncopsis)</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
